{"id":26,"parent_id":7,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":26,"title":"Matthew 20: Jesus Again Defines Greatness","subtitle":"","short_title":"Matthew 20: Jesus Again Defines Greatness","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-20-jesus-again-defines-greatness","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-20-jesus-again-defines-greatness"},[".heading",{"id":"head20","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-20-jesus-again-defines-greatness.head20"},["h1","Matthew 20"],[".subtitle","Jesus Again Defines Greatness"],[".intro","Do you like to feel important? What helps you feel important? Recognition? A position of leadership? Money? Success? The Pharisees of Jesus’ day thought they were very important. The reasons why they thought so are similar to the ways people define greatness and who or what is important today. As you read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/20"},"Matthew 20"],", however, be aware of what Jesus did and said that helps us understand what is important and what greatness is in His kingdom. It may also be helpful to realize that what was said and done in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/20"},"Matthew 20"],"was in the last month—perhaps even the last two weeks—before Jesus was crucified."]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Other Accounts of What You Read in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/20"},"Matthew 20"]],["p.para",{"id":"p601","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-20-jesus-again-defines-greatness.p601"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/20.17-34"},"Matthew 20:17–34"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/10.32-52"},"Mark 10:32–52"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/18.31-43"},"Luke 18:31–43"]]],[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f85","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-20-jesus-again-defines-greatness.f85"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/20"},"Matthew 20"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Householder"],"(v. 1)"],["td","Home owner"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Idle"],"(vv. 3, 6)"],["td","Doing nothing, not working"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Even"],"(v. 8)"],["td","Sundown, evening"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Steward"],"(v. 8)"],["td","A person who is in charge of things that belong to another"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Murmured"],"(v. 11)"],["td","Complained"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Wrought"],"(v. 12)"],["td","Worked"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Take that thine is"],"(v. 14)"],["td","Take what belongs to you—what you agreed to"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Scourge"],"(v. 19)"],["td","To beat with a whip that has jagged pieces of bone or stone in the ends"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Zebedee’s children"],"(v. 20)"],["td","James and John, the Apostles"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Indignation"],"(v. 24)"],["td","Strong displeasure"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Exercise dominion"],"(v. 25)"],["td","To be master over"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Minister"],"(vv. 26, 28)"],["td","Someone who serves and looks after the needs of another"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Ransom"],"(v. 28)"],["td","Payment (for those who are captive and need to be freed)"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Rebuked"],"(v. 31)"],["td","Encouraged strongly to stop"],["td"]]]]]],[".",{"id":"f86","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-20-jesus-again-defines-greatness.f86"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-028-2.gif"}],[".caption",["p",{"id":"lds-"},["span.emphasis","Whip used in scourging"]]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p617","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-20-jesus-again-defines-greatness.p617"},"Do either activity A or B as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/20"},"Matthew 20"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"The Parable of the Laborers"],[".",{"id":"f87","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-20-jesus-again-defines-greatness.f87"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-028-3.gif"}]],["p.para",{"id":"p618","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-20-jesus-again-defines-greatness.p618"},"The parable in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/20.1-16"},"Matthew 20:1–16"],"seems to be in response to the conversation Jesus had with Peter at the end of",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/19"},"Matthew 19"],". Peter had asked about what his reward would be for the sacrifice he felt he made to serve in the kingdom. Notice that the parable ends in much the same way",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/19"},"Matthew 19"],"ends."],[".figure",{"id":"f88","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-20-jesus-again-defines-greatness.f88"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","Make a chart in your notebook like the one below. Fill it in with information you learn in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/20.1-16"},"Matthew 20:1–16"],"."]]]],[".figure",{"id":"f89","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-20-jesus-again-defines-greatness.f89"},["table",["tbody",["tr",["th",["p.para",["b","The hour the laborers were hired"]]],["th",["p.para",["b","How much the man agreed to pay them"]]],["th",["p.para",["b","Hours worked"]]],["th",["p.para",["b","How much they were actually paid"]]]],["tr",["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]]],["tr",["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]]],["tr",["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]]],["tr",["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]]],["tr",["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]]]]]],[".figure",{"id":"f90","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-20-jesus-again-defines-greatness.f90"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","What do we learn from this parable about serving in the Lord’s kingdom?"]],["li",["span.label","3."],["p.para","What message of comfort can this parable have for converts to the Church?"]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-b.gif"}],"How You Can Become Great"],["p.para",{"id":"p646","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-20-jesus-again-defines-greatness.p646"},"In",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/20.20-28"},"Matthew 20:20–28"],"we read what Jesus said after the mother of James and John asked Him if her sons could have an important place in the kingdom of God."],[".figure",{"id":"f91","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-20-jesus-again-defines-greatness.f91"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","Choose what you think are three of the most important words or phrases in the Savior’s response to her request and explain why you chose each word or phrase."]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","List examples from",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/20.17-19,28-34"},"Matthew 20:17–19, 28–34"],"of how the Savior showed the kind of greatness He spoke of."]]]]]]],[".resources"]]]],"refs":null}
